<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCB6A74FF489B1E19B9BA52" pageId="48" pageNumber="806" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCB6A74FF489B1E19B9BA52" blockId="48.[175,1385,2374,3472]" lastBlockId="48.[1445,2648,280,397]" pageId="48" pageNumber="806">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFCB6A74FF489B1E1C0EB65A" bold="true" box="[180,526,3399,3432]" pageId="48" pageNumber="806">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Mount Missim Long-eared Bat is known only from twelve individuals, seven of which were captured in 2006. Additional sampling is needed to determineits full distribution and understand its ecology and taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
